definitions.definition: A road that is higher than the surrounding land and has drainage ditches at the sides
A main public road , especially a multi- lane , high-speed thoroughfare .
A way ; a path that leads to a certain destiny
examples: You're on a highway to greatness.

definitions.definition: Any public road for vehicular traffic.
Synonym of bus ( “ common connection for two or more circuits or components ” ) .
